flowRoot.flowPara: * Table shows Fixed effect's t-values. Absolute values greater than 2 corresponds to significant effects.
The effect of Cloze Predictability shows a negative relation with Gaze Duration. We would like to find a computer-based Predictability that mimics this effect

The ngram model (i.e. 4-word transition probability) with the addition of the local frequency generates a better model (with greater t-value and AIC). But after fitting the Cloze Predictability effect to the model residuals it is clear that it is not modeling the whole effect. It also makes the Frequency effect drop on its t-value.

Comparing both models of AWD-LSTM (before and after performing the fine tuning with an small corpus of texts similar to the test corpus) it is possible to observe an enhanced estimation of Predictability. Not only on an increase in the (absolute value) of the t-value and the AIC, but also in a lower decrease for the Frequency effect.
The AWD-LSTM model seems to capture similar aspects of word predictions than the Ngram model, but the RNN-based model has a behaviour more similar to the Cloze Predictability.

Both LSA and FastText model Natural Language by word embeddings, that represents words in a multidimensional semantic space. Modelling the Predictability as the semantic closeness to its context (the previous w words) makes little difference to the LMMs.
